<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Temperatures are reaching triple digits in the San Fernando Valley, and brush 
fires are raging across Southern California (June 29). So why is it that on my 
way home from work yesterday I saw roughly 20 people throw burning cigarettes 
from car windows? Can we please use our heads? 
</P>
<P>
 ELINOR E. DUQUE 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 
</P>
