<HEADLINE>
<P>
ETHIOPIAN RULING PARTY WINS ASSEMBLY VOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The ruling Ethiopian People's Revolutionary Democratic Front and its allies 
scored an overwhelming victory by securing 484 of the 547 seats in June 5 
elections for a constituent assembly, the Election Board said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The new assembly is mandated to approve a new constitution for Ethiopia 
following the overthrow of the Marxist military dictatorship in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 The election was boycotted by groups opposed to constitutional proposals for 
local autonomy that they fear could destroy Ethiopian unity. 
</P>
