WORLD CUP USA '94 / ROUND OF 16; SPOTLIGHT; BORN ON FOURTH OF JULY? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB HUGHES, The Times of London 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 And this on U.S.-Brazil: 
</P>
<P>
 "Will American interest be sustained to the end? If there is to be a turning 
point in this new experience for the United States, it could come on Monday, 
July 4, Independence Day. Then the rookies of the host nation travel to Palo 
Alto, to attempt to pull off what might be called 'the greatest shock in 
sporting history' against Brazil. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 "Their Serbian manager, Bora Milutinovic, is working on psychology. He 
believes football is a game of the mind and hopes that the innocence, the 
arrogance of the American soul, will enable his players to ignore the gulf in 
class." ROB HUGHES, The Times of London 
</P>
