<TEXT>
<P>
 Everyone from the president of the country to Coach Carlos Alberto Parreira's 
mother has suggested changes in Brazil's lineup.So why not Pele? 
</P>
<P>
 In a column last week for USA Today, Pele advised Parreira to make personnel 
moves involving six players. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will be necessary to try these different suggestions during practice 
sessions in Santa Clara, Calif., because Brazil cannot play any worse," Pele 
concluded. 
</P>
<P>
 Brazil is 2-0-1, scoring six goals and allowing only one. RANDY HARVEY 
