<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / ROUND OF 16; SPOTLIGHT; ON THEIR BEST BEHAVIOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Good news for the U.S. team. It may win something from this World Cup after 
all -- the FIFA Fairplay Contest. 
</P>
<P>
 Based on an assessment of a team's conduct during the games, FIFA is tracking 
the Fairplay sweepstakes. Criteria include respect toward opponents, behavior 
of team officials and behavior of the crowd. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. team is ahead so far, having behaved better than the Swiss, the 
Brazilians -- who are tied with the Belgians -- and the Mexicans. 
</P>
<P>
 Next, the swimsuit competition. JULIE CART 
</P>
