<P>
CANADIAN OLYMPIAN DOMINATES DIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paige Gordon, who represented Canada in the 1992 Olympics, finished in first 
place in the senior women's three-meter competition Sunday at the Southern 
California Diving Invitational at Marguerite Swimming and Diving Complex. 
</P>
<P>
 Gordon, 21, representing the Vancouver Aquatic Centre, finished the day 
strong, scoring 444.25 points.But Mission Viejo Nadadores' Sandy Zubrin also 
was impressive, finishing second with 435.75 points. 
</P>
<P>
 The Nadadores' Summer Brown, who was first in the competition Friday and 
Saturday, was third with 426.35. 
</P>
<P>
 Zubrin, who recently was third in platform diving at the Four Nations Meet in 
Tianjin, China, and 11th in the China Open, expects stiff competition from 
Gordon and Eileen Richetelli, who won the women's competition at the 1991 Pan 
American Games. 
</P>
<P>
 Erica Sorgi, 12, who won the one- and three-meter competition in the 11- to 
12-year-old division Friday and Saturday, finished eighth in the senior 
competition with 401.20 points. Sorgi, representing the Nadadores, was sixth in 
platform diving in the 11- to 12-year-old division. 
</P>
<P>
 In the men's senior one-meter, Karl Fix of the Vancouver Aquatic Centre was 
first with 513.50 points. Drew Jackson of Tualatin Hills Dive Club was second 
with 456 points and Craig Lincoln was third with 449.60. 
</P>
<P>
 Tyce Routson, who took first in the three-meter Saturday, did not compete 
Sunday, but will participate in today's senior platform event. ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
