<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 20 SUSPECTED DRUNK DRIVERS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities on Sunday said they have arrested 20 motorists on suspicion of 
drunk driving since the start of the Fourth of July weekend. They also reported 
two serious accidents. 
</P>
<P>
 Motorists were arrested between 6 p.m. Friday and 6 a.m. Sunday, California 
Highway Patrol officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 At least one major injury accident that occurred in Westlake on Saturday may 
have been alcohol-related, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Visser, 29, of Thousand Oaks was arrested on suspicion of drunk driving 
after his car collided with one driven by Corey Klein, 16, of Westlake Village, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 4 p.m. at Westlake Boulevard and Potrero Road. 
Visser's passenger, Elise Phillips, received major injuries, authorities said. 
She was listed Sunday in fair condition at Westlake Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Visser was being held on $5,000 bail at Ventura County Jail on Sunday. He is 
scheduled to be arraigned Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 In another major injury accident Saturday, a car driving west on California 
126 east of Hopper Canyon Road caused a two-vehicle crash and left the scene, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Six people were injured in the head-on collision that occurred about 7:15 
p.m., the CHP said. An older-model white or yellow Honda Civic driving west on 
California 126 swerved into the eastbound lanes, causing the other driver to 
turn sharply to the right to avoid an accident. 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Geraze, 43, of Valencia then lost control and her car swerved into the 
westbound lanes and hit a car driven by Robert Urger, 30, of North Hollywood. 
The Honda fled, traveling west on California 126 toward Fillmore, the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials at Santa Paula Hospital and Ventura County Medical Center said 
Sunday that the two drivers and their passengers were all in good or fair 
condition. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
