<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: AUTHORITIES CONTINUE SEARCH FOR MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County authorities Sunday continued to search for a man who has seven 
outstanding felony warrants and eluded sheriff's deputies last week during a 
foot chase. 
</P>
<P>
 David Matthew Clawson, 21, of St. Charles, Mo., was last seen hiding in a 
cornfield in El Rio, authorities said.He fled after deputies chased him and his 
17-year-old girlfriend, who was later taken into custody and transported back 
to Missouri. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's told his girlfriend he's not going to be taken alive," Ventura County 
Sheriff's Detective Charles Harwood said. "We think he's hanging out in the 
Ventura-Oxnard area." 
</P>
<P>
 Harwood said Clawson is a suspected drug dealer who was raised in Ventura, 
although his parents have since moved to St. Charles. Authorities suspect that 
he came to California because he would have a bigger drug clientele. Since 
returning to the area, he has stayed at the Doubletree Hotel in Ventura, the 
Radisson Suite Hotel in Oxnard and the Oxnard Hilton, Harwood said. 
</P>
<P>
 Clawson left St. Charles on June 27, and authorities there said he is wanted 
in connection with a variety of crimes, including numerous burglaries. 
</P>
<P>
 "If there's something stolen out of his neighborhood, that's who we suspect," 
St. Charles County Sheriff's Detective Bob Carmody said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carmody said it is likely that Missouri authorities will extradite Clawson if 
he is caught. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said they do not know if Clawson is armed. He is 6 feet, 1 inch 
tall, weighs about 175 pounds, has black hair and brown eyes and a scar on his 
chin. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone who sees Clawson should call their local police department. PEGGY Y. 
LEE 
</P>
