<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joint Ventures Told to Form Trade Unions: The government has ordered 
foreign-financed joint ventures to set up official trade unions by the end of 
the year, blaming a lack of organizations for a spate of deadly workplace 
accidents. Zhang Dinghua, vice chairman of the state-controlled All-China 
Federation of Trade Unions, said just 12% of foreign-financed joint ventures 
had unions, the official Xinhua news agency reported.Zhang also pledged a major 
drive to put official unions into the 95% of Chinese township enterprises that 
still have no worker organizations, a move that would bring tens of millions of 
workers under the federation umbrella. Zhang said official unions are needed to 
protect workers from unscrupulous or negligent employers, citing "some serious 
problems" among foreign companies that hire Chinese laborers. 
</P>
