</P>
<P>
 Comedy writer Tony Peyser, on the battle between Mattel and Hasbro for control 
of a British company with rights to sell Scrabble outside North America: "The 
deal could be worth more than $70 million. Or $210 million if it lands on a 
triple word score." 
</P>
<P>
 Comic Ed Markey, on car rental companies having only one question on their car 
return forms: They ask, "Did you buy gas?" This makes no sense. If they are 
limited to only one question, shouldn't it be: "Did you ever utter the phrase, 
'Screw it, it's a rental'?" 
</P>
