<P>
PACKAGE DEALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scope Packaging Inc. has been manufacturing state-of-the-art packaging for 
almost 30 years at its plant in Orange.The firm makes packaging for Hitachi, 
Knott's Berry Farm, Canon, Rubbermaid and other well-known companies. Sergio 
Gonzalez, right, checks the color quality on one of the boxes. Scope has about 
100 employees at its 70,000-square-foot facility. The company buys pre-cut 
corrugated cardboard and uses a series of presses to print high-quality 
"graphic messages." William Flynn is president of the privately held, 
family-owned business. 
