<TEXT>
<P>
 Current Account Deficit Falls Sharply: The figure fell to $80 million in May 
from $250 million in April, the Bank of Korea said.The reduction came as the 
country's trade account showed a surplus of $50 million in May, after deficits 
during the four previous months, the central bank said. The cumulative current 
account deficit during the first five months of this year amounted to $2.68 
billion, nearly five times that of the same period last year. Bank officials 
said the current account deficit for this year is expected to fall below the 
original projection of $2.5 billion because exports are expected to continue to 
gain throughout the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
